<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1927,2023]" lastBlockId="22.[151,1436,151,316]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="279" pageId="21" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,418,1927,1953]" pageId="21" pageNumber="278">Diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
Moths of the 
<emphasis box="[580,739,1927,1953]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="278">annulignatha-</emphasis>
group share a dark broad lanceolate forewing with two small, ill-defined yellow costal spots, and sometimes a larger yellow dorsal spot. Forewing length running from 8.5 to 9.0 mm, length approximately 3.1â€¾3.5 times of the maximum width. In male genitalia, uncus bifurcate apically; gnathos circular, with a distinct anteromedian plate in some species; costa with a large process near base; sacculus separated from the valva entirely or only distally, often produced to one or two processes distally. In female genitalia, ductus bursae partly sclerotized, or membranous with granules; signum usually absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="279" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,151,316]" pageId="22" pageNumber="279">
The 
<emphasis box="[250,409,255,281]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="279">annulignatha-</emphasis>
group is one of the smallest groups, including one described species from 
<collectingCountry box="[1236,1306,255,281]" name="China" pageId="22" pageNumber="279">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wang, 2006) (in Wang 2006 a)" authorityName="in Wang" authorityYear="2006" baseAuthorityName="Wang" baseAuthorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Cosmopterigidae" genus="Meleonoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="279" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifoliolata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="279">M. bifoliolata</emphasis>
(Wang, 2006) (in 
<bibRefCitation author="Wang, S. X." box="[400,544,289,316]" pageId="22" pageNumber="279" pagination="1 - 29" refId="ref24677" refString="Wang, S. X. (2006 a) The Cryptolechia Zeller (Lepidoptera: Oecophoridae) of China (III): Checklist and descriptions of new species. Zootaxa, 1195 (1), 1 - 29. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1195.1.1" type="journal article" year="2006">Wang 2006a</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and four new species described herein.
</paragraph>
